caption: Really top notch ice cream. We like to have lunch here.

My family has ordered take out from Earnest 4 or 5 times in the past few months and we have never been disappointed. The flavor is inventive and spot on in everything from their sandwiches to their pies to their bread pudding to their gnocchi (seriously, we've tried almost everything on their menu). Their prices are reasonable, their app is better than other restaurants', and they even have great wine deals. I have avoided raving about them because I don't want more items to go out of stock, but I want them to last forever because they're by far my favorite food establishment in the area, so please eat their delicious food to help keep them alive!
Cute heated outdoor space with quick and prompt service. The milkshakes and food are on the smaller portion size for the price that they are.

I found Earnest when looking for a accessible new lunch spot. Currently set up for take out or outdoor seating with heaters.  I ordered their mushroom 'philly' and it did not disappoint. Cheesy, flavorful, umami. Hit the spot on a cooler day. Smaller than the average american portion, but higher quality ingredients. Top notch cappuccino. I've ordered from there since.

Delightful, quirky spot for anything you could ever want - sandwiches, coffee, brunch, ice cream, boozy milkshakes, cocktails! Super cute patio, a small but creative and tasty menu, and tons of cheeky character all around. Can't wait to come here again and again. My favorites so far are the cheese plate appetizer and the hot toddy. And the Dolly Parton bathroom.
A welcome addition to the area, with a relaxing outdoor space and heaters for the winter.

Ordered delivery this weekend; sandwiches for now, ice cream for tonight!  The pulled pork sandwich was tasty, definitely recommend adding an egg to it! Also got a double latte that was excellent. One of the items we ordered was not available, so we were refunded, but when we dug into the bag, we saw that we were given some bread pudding to make up for the issue. My husband enjoyed that surprise greatly!  I've been a fan of Gracie's Ice Cream for a while, and happy to see them expand to a bigger menu/new space at Earnest Drinks. I only wish I was still working in Kendall Sq, so I could go for lunch in person. Next time we plan to try takeout so we can partake in some of the adult beverages.  SUPER excited for my ice cream flight, a great way to sample a bunch of flavors without committing to a whole pint.

Yes! Yes yes yes yes yes! Lots of outdoor, spaciously spaced seating. Friendly and quick service -- I'd barely gotten through 2 pages of my book before my drink and food arrived. And boy were they delicious! I was gonna only drink 2/3 of my whisky pandan frappe (cuz, waistline) but yeah...nope. That disappeared real quick. Perfectly balanced, strong pandan flavor and good smoky whisky flavor, without being cloying or overwhelming. And the mushroom "cheesesteak" was LUSCIOUS. Really incredible, umami and earthy and rich but not too heavy, with light and slightly sweet bread.  Sammies and other bites will run you $6-10. Frappes $13. They have other drinks as well, and desserts (Gracies Ice Cream). I can't wait to come back!
